<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1094,1913]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,1094,1120]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1961" box="[320,559,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lusitanica">
<emphasis box="[320,559,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Callitriche lusitanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Mediterranean Basin, but its distribution is poorly known. It is widespread and abundant in the centre and west of the Iberian Peninsula and occurs in North Africa in 
<collectingCountry box="[1343,1447,1131,1157]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,223,1166,1192]" name="Algeria" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[282,368,1166,1192]" name="Tunisia" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, as well as from the islands of Sardinia and Sicily east to 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1078,1166,1192]" name="Israel" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Bazos, I. &amp; Caria, M. C. &amp; Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J." box="[1093,1341,1166,1193]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref15669" refString="Lansdown, R. V., Bazos, I., Caria, M. C., Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J. (2017) New distribution and taxonomic information on Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) in the Mediterranean region. Phytotaxa 313: 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 313.1.6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lansdown 
<emphasis box="[1218,1268,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Prancl, J. &amp; Fehrer, J. &amp; Caklova, P. &amp; Bambasova, V. &amp; Lucanova, M. &amp; Kaplan, Z." pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="1016 - 1041" refId="ref16234" refString="Prancl, J., Fehrer, J., Caklova, P., Bambasova, V., Lucanova, M. &amp; Kaplan, Z. (2020) Intricate evolutionary history of Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) taxa elucidated by a combination of DNA sequencing and genome size. Taxon 69 (5): 1016 - 1041. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12315" type="journal article" year="2020">
Prančl 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[286,387,1203,1229]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
it appears to be restricted to the coastal lowlands from Safi north to Tangiers, where it is not uncommon south of Rabat (
<figureCitation box="[448,537,1238,1264]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,712,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-280@3.[151,1435,710,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Known distribution of Callitriche spp. in Morocco. A. C. brutia subsp. brutia, with insert map showing the position of Morocco in northwestern Africa. B. C. brutia subsp. naftolskyi. C. C. cribrosa. D. C. lusitanica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875717/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1094,1913]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,448,1274,1300]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
—Throughout much of its range, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1961" box="[848,995,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lusitanica">
<emphasis box="[848,995,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">C. lusitanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in gravel- or cobble-bed rivers on siliceous soils, where it may 
<taxonomicName box="[510,629,1310,1336]" form="large" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" rank="form">form large</taxonomicName>
stands in the main channel and backwaters (
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Bazos, I. &amp; Caria, M. C. &amp; Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J." box="[1150,1407,1310,1337]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref15669" refString="Lansdown, R. V., Bazos, I., Caria, M. C., Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J. (2017) New distribution and taxonomic information on Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) in the Mediterranean region. Phytotaxa 313: 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 313.1.6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lansdown 
<emphasis box="[1278,1330,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[136,237,1347,1373]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
although it has been recorded from slow-flowing water (
<bibRefCitation author="Fennane, M. &amp; Ibn Tattou, M. &amp; Ouyahya, A. &amp; El Oualidi, J." box="[872,1098,1346,1373]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" refId="ref14699" refString="Fennane, M., Ibn Tattou, M., Ouyahya, A. &amp; El Oualidi, J. (2007) Flore pratique du Maroc: manuel de determination des plantes vasculaires: Angiospermae (Leguminosae - Lentibulariaceae), Vol. 2. Rabat Institut Scientifique, Rabat, 636 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Fennane 
<emphasis box="[975,1024,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), it is more frequent in seasonal waterbodies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1094,1913]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1418,1444]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Notes:</emphasis>
—The Iberian Peninsula and 
<collectingCountry box="[587,688,1419,1445]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
appear to represent the core distribution area of this species, however scattered records from the larger Mediterranean islands, other countries in North Africa, and from 
<collectingCountry box="[1228,1290,1454,1480]" name="Israel" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Israel</collectingCountry>
suggest that it may have a similar distribution to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prancl" baseAuthorityName="Warburg &amp; Eig" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[604,901,1490,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="brutia" subSpecies="naftolskyi">
<emphasis box="[604,705,1490,1517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">C. brutia</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[792,901,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">naftolskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is clearly under-recorded throughout much of its range and since it is poorly represented in herbaria, it is difficult to define its distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1094,1913]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1562,1588]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1961" box="[370,614,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lusitanica">
<emphasis box="[370,614,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Callitriche lusitanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1058,1274,1562,1588]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[1058,1179,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[136,237,1599,1625]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Morocco</collectingCountry>
by the combination of the translucent leaves that are not connate at the base, and the broadly-winged fruit that are blackish when mature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1094,1913]" box="[189,1366,1670,1697]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Illustrations:</emphasis>
—Figures in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[493,725,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" refId="ref15552" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2008) Water starworts of Europe. BSBI Handbook No. 11. Botanical Society of the British Isles, London, 180 pp." type="book" year="2008">Lansdown [2008: 24</bibRefCitation>
(5-5x), 75, 77]; Plates in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Bazos, I. &amp; Caria, M. C. &amp; Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J." box="[1012,1362,1670,1697]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref15669" refString="Lansdown, R. V., Bazos, I., Caria, M. C., Troia, A. &amp; Wieringa, J. J. (2017) New distribution and taxonomic information on Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) in the Mediterranean region. Phytotaxa 313: 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 313.1.6" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lansdown 
<emphasis box="[1136,1185,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. (2017: 96–97)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
